Mexico strikes gold in Pan American Games
2011-10-17 06:46:14 GMT
GUADALAJARA, Mexico, Oct. 17 (Xinhua) -- Mexico won its first two gold medals in the 16th Pan American Games on Sunday.The host country's first gold came from Oscar Soto in the men's modern pentathlon. Guatemala's Andrei Gheorghe finished second with 18-year-old Chilean Esteban Bustos in third place.Hours later, Irma Contreras got to the top of the podium and won the second gold medal for Mexico by defeating Doris Patino from Colombia 4-3 in the -67kg taekwondo final.
